    "body": "Its easy to add trailing semicolons in Python when switching between C code. Luckily, this is allowed by Python. But Cython throws a rather cryptic error message here:\n```\ncdef foo():\n    cdef int i\n\ncdef bar():\n    cdef int i;\n```\nResults in \n```\nError compiling Cython file:\n------------------------------------------------------------\n...\n\ncdef foo():\n    cdef int i\n\ncdef bar():\n    cdef int i;\n             ^\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nphi4.pyx:10:14: Syntax error in C variable declaration\n```\nTook me a while to figure out that its the trailing semicolon. IMHO Cython should match the Python behavior and allow trailing semicolons...\n\nMigrated from http://trac.cython.org/ticket/832",
